value.0: This pig-tailed girl seems out of place in this store, cheerfully looking at her cards, one at a time.
"Oh, my mommy doesn't like me betting for money.  We could bet for cards, though!"
"So, which deck do you want to play with?"
"That would be oh so very nice," she rapidly jabbers away.  "I use my goblin deck.  Some people think goblins are dirty and mean, but I think they're cute.  Do you think they're cute?"

"Oh yes.  And they're brave too!  Everyone thinks they're the lowest of the low.  Even the greenest of adventurers slaughter them like they were barely an obstacle.  But the brave goblins fight as best they can, against unwinnable odds.  How courageous they are!"
"Of course they are!  And look at how cute they are."  She holds up a picture of one of her goblin cards.  "See?"
Say, let's play, but perhaps we can make a little bet?
Say, would you like to play a game of Creatures?
Goblins cute?  I never really thought about it . . .
I never really thought of them as brave.
On second thought, I have to go.
Excuse me little girl, I need to go puke at your excessive cuteness.
How about we just play, okay?
